The paper discusses a Sybil-resistant P2P system and proposes a Sybil detection mechanism. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as well as Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of social networks and lookup schemes also suggests the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the focus on Sybil attacks and defense mechanisms indicates the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
